This year, the women have won the Nobel Prize in physics in all fields
A record five women today in Stockholm has taken over from the hands of the Swedish King Carl XVI Gustaf of this year's Nobel Prize in technical categories and for literature.
In addition to the four scientists among them was the German writer Herta Müller of Romanian origin.
The Nobel Prize for medicine have received two American biologists Elizabeth Blackburnová and Carol Greiderová together with their fellow countrymen Jack Szostakem for research in the field of chromosomes.
The prize for chemistry was given an Israeli Ada Jonathová together with the Americans, and Thomas Steitzem for clarification of the structure and function of the ribosome.
The last was the Nobel Prize in economics, won by American Ostromová Elinor and her compatriot Oliver Williamson for the analysis of economic governance.
The only professional categories, which this year brought no holders of, the physics.
This award today took scientists Charles Kao for research in the field of optical fibres and George Smith and Willard Boyle for the invention of CCD chip, which is the basis of all digital cameras, fax or astronomical telescopes.
Each winning took a diploma, the Nobel medal and a certificate of profit financial rewards.
The totals for each category of the 10 million Swedish crowns (about 25 million) .
If it is decorated in each of them more reward is divided between them.
Traditionally, most expected the Nobel Prize for Peace has already received this afternoon in Oslo, Norway, U. S. President Barack Obama.
In his speech, he acknowledged the kontroverznost his awards, because it is only at the beginning of his career and also heads the country resulting in two wars - in Iraq and Afghanistan.
In defense of its policy, but added that some wars are necessary for fighting in a situation of peace, even if the price is high.
