The secret of the glow over Norway: the Russians tested a missile
Over Norway, it was possible to observe a special light effect of unknown origin.
The Russian Ministry of Defence only yesterday acknowledged that near the Norwegian border, tested an intercontinental ballistic missile.
Start again but was unsuccessful and the missile known as type " Bulava ", which was originally intended to be the pride of the Russian army, is slowly becoming a Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir Putin.
Neither his repeated presence at the missile tests had to the success of the test flights at the appropriate effect.
Bulava most ever took off or damaged in the air.
In the Russian newspaper was the " Bulava " writes as a " rocket, which can not fly. "
The rocket, which can not fly but shine
This in turn was the 13th experiment was conducted initially normally.
Until the end of the flight was again damaged technical apparatus.
Apparently, the engine exploded in the third stage of the rocket.
This time, " Bulava " starting from the nuclear submarine Dmitry Donskij, which was below the surface of the White Sea.
This type of missiles, allows the firing from the ship, which is on the move, and at the same time.
Therefore, it is likely that the mysterious light over Norway caused by the unidentified flying object was actually broken " Bulava ".
Indeed, the Norwegians from the first moment he had no doubt that it is a Russian rocket.
The generals this time prevents a claim that can not speak clearly a failure.
The first two stages of the rocket and an accident to hit the third.
In previous cases, the engines broke down right in the first instance.
Although completely flawless or may not have been a test start, the leadership of the Department of Defense considers that only six out of thirteen.
Almost 50 percent success rate so filled with optimism and generals and still maintains that the " Bulava " would one day fly without problems and that even hypersonických can carry up to ten nuclear units with a maximum total weight of 1.15 tons.
