Filipino militants are still holding back more than 50 persons, children released to freedom
Today, the gunmen in the south of the Philippines kidnapped 75 people, including some primary school pupils and their teachers.
She said the AFP, which was initially reported only 65 kidnapped.
All 17 children have been detained were released after eight hours, including one teacher.
The abduction occurred in the province of Agusan del Sur.
Approximately 19 armed men, they are using the hostages as a shield to escape from the police.
Local negotiators are now trying to agree on the release of the remaining hostages.
According to the AFP, the militants belonging to the New People's Army (NPA which is an armed component of the Communist Party of the Philippines (CPP) .
According to the AP police originally kidnapper pursued because of the violence, which has claimed the processing of accounts between two local family clans.
In the south of the Philippines in the province of Maguindanao was due to the recent massacre, in which were killed 57 people, declared martial law.
Among the victims of the massacre of 23 November associated with the election to the office of governor was 30 journalists.
On suspicion of involvement in the massacre was arrested the governor of the province and his father Andal Ampatuan, the patriarch of the influential House Ampatuanů.
On the island of Mindanao are also employed by Muslim separatists.
But they resume on Tuesday with the Philippine government peace talks.
