With the film in cinemas arise from critics and the public
Nelson Mandela
His full name Nelson Rolihlahla Mandela was born on July 18, 1918, in South Africa.
In 1988, he received the Sakharov prize for freedom of thought, in 1993, then together with de Klerk, the Nobel Peace Prize.
President of the Republic of South Africa was in the period 1994-1999.
High expectations, as it comes to the public at a time when in South Africa and to the preparations for the world championships in football, but reports of increasing racial hatred and discrimination against black people by the ruling at the same time, the media on the part of the majority.
