Ten agreements concluded by the Iraqi Ministry of the oil industry with foreign oil companies, suggesting that the Chinese, Russian and European oil companies are prepared to play an important role in the reconstruction of Iraq's oil industry, the decades of war and sanctions.
American companies left with equity participation just two of 10 fields auctioned.
Seven US companies pay for their participation in the second auction, which began on Friday.
Only one has lost a bid.
Two U. S. companies have reached agreements on the field, which was auctioned in June.
The participation of American oil giants in an open Iraq's oil industry, surprised analysts.
Iraq finally opened the door after six years of war and the American companies that have here in the first place on the way Asians and Europeans, " said Ruba Husari, editor of the Iraq Oil Forum, online news.
It will be a long time before something else will be in Iraq for sale.
Concerns about safety, highlighted by massive coordinated bomb attacks on Tuesday, and political instability, as well as the withdrawal of the U. S. military is likely to discourage U. S. companies from more intensive business in Iraq, which has the third - largest proven reserves of raw materials, analysts say.
American companies have in some cases at a disadvantage, in particular, the Chinese and other government - controlled energy firms have significantly lower operating costs and are more prone to risk, because they are not accountable to shareholders.
Exxon Mobil and Occidental Petroleum Inc. is the only U. S. companies, which have concluded an agreement with the Ministry.
Leading American companies such as Chevron and ConocoPhillips, which maintain close contacts with the Iraqi Ministry of oil, and to offer technical assistance in the past years, left empty - handed.
The Russian company Lukoil and Gazprom were the top shareholders in two of the contracts that were awarded at the end of the week.
The China National Petroleum Corp. was involved in the bids on more contracts than any other company and left with large stakes in two major contracts for the fields.
We all know that China is seeking to become the main economic, as well as technological power, said a spokesman for the Ministry of oil Assam Jihad.
We believe that the Chinese company will be comparable to the competition and to honor their commitments to Iraq.
The company, which have been selected for the submission of tenders, which were then compared to the price of a barrel and the Ministry is willing to pay for the strengthening of the current level in each field.
