The Turkish justice dismissed for the Kurdish side and this decision brings with it grave consequences.
Turkey's Constitutional Court on Friday decided to cancel the main pro - Kurdish party in the country. the decision immediately triggered a protest demonstration s in the Kurdish community in the south - east of the country and in Istanbul.
This decision may greatly complicate the task of government, which is trying to provide a hand of friendship to the Kurdish community and try to attempt to end 25 years of conflict.
Party for the Democratic Society Party (DTP) was disbanded because it has become " activities against the independence of the state and its indivisible unity, " said the chairman of the Supreme Court Hasim Kilic told reporters after four days of the negotiations.
The decision was taken unanimously by the 11 judges, when for the dissolution of the parties to the most - needed seven votes, he said, adding that 37 party cadres, including its president and the ban to participate in political life for a period of five years.
The judge also announced the abolition of parliamentary immunity, which was used by Mr and Mrs Tugluková and confiscation of property by the Ministry of Finance.
The party has 21 seats in Parliament (500) .
The Party leadership has indicated before The verdict that members of Parliament rather than leave it served as members of no political affiliation.
The decision is a continuation of a process initiated in 2007, the Prosecutor of the Court of Cassation, which accused the DTP of obedience to the " commands " Party of Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) , which Ankara and many countries regard as a terrorist organization.
Many observers believe that the DTP is a legal political showcase rebels from the PKK.
Page assures that the PKK has no " essential link ", but refuses to label it a terrorist organization, and calls on the government to negotiating with it.
The verdict comes at a time when the government gives the Kurdish community, a friendly hand and offers a range of measures to strengthen their rights and trying to limit the support of Kurds against the PKK and end the conflict.
The DTP executives confirmed that the dissolution of the parties could lead to a renewal of tensions in the southeast Anatolia, where in recent weeks, many demonstrations against the conditions under which the PKK leader Abdullah Öcalan in clashes with the police.
From the notification of the decision of justice, thousands of protesters gathered in front of the seat of the DTP in Diyarbakir, a big city in the southeast, mostly inhabited by the Kurds.
The police used tear grenades and water cannon, the demonstrators threw Molotov cocktails again and fired stones from slings.
Also in Istanbul, about a hundred people.
After the verdict, Mr Türk said that the decision of Justice " will deepening despair.
Turkey is not the question (the Kurds, red. ) to resolve the ban, said in the press.
The government, consisting of a party came from the Islamist movement, also condemned the decision.
We are in principle against the interference of the parties.
It does not solve anything, said Energy Minister Taner Yildiz.
This decision is an absolute shooting democratic proposals, which were initiated by the government, said political scientist Ahmet Insel.
Of course, we can wait for reaction from the PKK, he said.
On Thursday, the PKK subscribed to one of the most deadly attacks in the north of Turkey, which killed three days earlier, seven soldiers.
