The study of the junk
A partial success for students: after a year of picketing on Thursday, finally drove the Länder ministers of culture: at the conference of ministers of culture and the university presidents, both sides agreed that it will improve conditions for the bachelor's degree and a Masters.
Students should in future be able to handle their study.
In particular, they agreed to reduce the load tests: the principle that each learning module to end one single test.
In addition, it should check the workload for learners, and should ensure " fair and affordable rates.
Politicians and universities want to simplify the recognition tests between universities in Germany and abroad.
The federal countries undertake to create a more flexible common structural assignment for Bachelor's and master's study.
The derogations should cease to exist.
Fewer tests
From the start of the student protests in the worm had ministers of culture and university the winged words in the mouth of a better education.
Now, for the first time, they are filled with specific content.
The so - called accreditation Council concluded that the number of tests to drastically reduce in part: " each module will be terminated, as a one test, " says the 30 - page report, which is part of the approval of new studies.
" Significantly lower examination burden, " said the chairman of the accreditation Council Reinhold Grimm, should be " stopped mistakes, which significantly limited the performance of studies. "
The study should be " performance " in the future, " the decisive criterion " in implementation.
Modules and the contents of the " hard " to " unnecessarily restrict the choice of learning
Courses.
Students should be " entitled to a space, which allows and encourages individual initiative.
The rules are to apply for approval of the new study, after a review, but also for the current study.
You need to be " přeakreditovat " every five years - which, however, means that it will take until 2015 before they checked all fields of study.
Is responsible for around ten German accreditation agencies that are subject to accreditation councils established by the Länder.
The Ministers of Culture in October called " strongly " of the Land to the agency, in ways so that the content of the curriculum was too large and examination system was strict.
In some federal countries have universities and colleges by the provincial ministries to agree on the appropriate measures.
As the only country in the Rhineland - Palatinate pledged additional funds for the further development of the Bologna process.
The money should pay for high school, in particular, and study advice, and to strengthen the test and foreign offices.
It wants the country and colleges to spend ten million euros.
At the beginning of 2010, the government intends to submit to Parliament an amendment to the higher education Act.
According to the study by the end of the module should be required only a single test.
The Formation of study should be more flexible, to be guaranteed by the recognition of tests from other universities and to facilitate access to the disclosure of the master's degree.
By the end of next year should be inspected performance of all study subjects in the country.
The government and the opposition on Thursday again about the study conditions in the country.
In addition to praise as well as criticism of the resolution.
The Board of directors of the Federal higher education groups called for to the creation of education policy in the future, " behind closed doors " of ministers and university presidents.
At the latest strike would " do it should at least speak a word " as well as students of the person concerned.
The future scholars also receive support from the president of the Conference of presidents of higher education (HRK) , Margrety Wintermantelové: " We need the experience of students, " she said Thursday at a meeting with the ministers of culture, with which hrk advice on the reform of the common report.
According to the union of Education and Science (GEW) , Bonn resolution did not go far enough: they want the legal right to which every graduate with a bachelor's degree to allow access to a follow - up master's degree.
Second, the Land to ensure that today's generation of students for undergraduate courses was tomorrow, there are insufficient places in the Masters ' fields of study with the best conditions, " said a member of the board of directors GEW Andreas Keller.
