Worlds dreams
Some see the images in the waking state and hear voices that other people can see and hear.
Not only the mentally ill or in the drug intoxication blur the boundaries between imagination and reality.
Until this occurs during sleep, everything is fine.
If we closed our eyes in a dark room, we may surround the and delusions.
But who is experiencing a dream - like states of vigilance, hear and see things that others can see and hear, is in today's the Western world for a fool or a drug dependent, or at least as a result.
But such images and voices that do not only for the mentally ill or in the drug intoxication.
Guilt is our imagination: the same neuronal processes that allow us to design houses, paint pictures or write novels, here and there, they will take care of it, that the border between the dream and reality.
The Dreams of the altered state of consciousness can occur in various forms, at best, we call them a vision, at worst, delusional.
Even if the initiator and the effect may vary, but it mystical visions Hildegard von Bingen, the drug experiences of the Prophet New - Age Carlos Castaneda, shamanic states of mania, psychoses and hallucinations derived from similar processes.
Hallucinations or visions arise when there is a derailment of the balance of neuronal transmitters of the brain - particularly dopamine, serotonin and norepinephrine, and interaction between the different parts of the brain is disturbed.
A comprehensive hallucinations and wandering thoughts occur very often in schizophrenic psychosis.
Gravity has no power over him
The link between the dreams and delusions of employed doctors and philosophers since antiquity.
Aristotle understood as a form of hallucination, a dream in the waking state, Wilhelm Griesinger, one of the founders of modern psychology, said in 1861 " the great similarity ravings with dream states, the Sigmund Freud was a dream even " psychosis, with all the nonsense, delusions, deception of the senses. "
It is the autumn of 2001, Henning T. is amended in comic figure.
His body is a two - dimensional and brightly colored.
Gravity has no power over him, floating in the ceiling of the room.
Feels kick up the backside.
Behind him, a winged figure with the devil red blood grimace, baring teeth.
Chasing him, kick him in the heavy, fiery shoes, throwing him on the wall, he feels the pain throughout the body.
Loud, bad voices from the walls and on the radio.
We can not tolerate voices that curse and insult him.
Henning T. pulls two cables from the stereo, zauzlí it into a loop and fastened it on a hook on the ceiling.
Stand up to one speaker and you can loop around the neck.
Jump.
Loop.
Learn, a chorus of voices tearing his eardrums, " go to the clinic to be treated! "
It is now 40 years old, has had six acute psychosis, the last two years, the first in nearly 20 years ago.
They were running LSD.
His diagnosis is schizoafektivní paranoid psychosis, besides a manic - depressive, he takes medication for depression, mania, schizophrenia.
He learned to live with their disease, three years is married.
In psychosis, I had the worst fear and deep doubts, he says.
The Ghosts are a terrible reality
About one percent of people get sick at least once in a lifetime of schizophrenia in psychiatric clinics is the second most commonly depression treatment of disease.
Acute schizophrenic psychosis are not affected most of them can distinguish between the internal and external world, moving into přebuzeného condition, that can lead to hallucinations, velikostním, or the illusion of persecution.
Especially widespread is hearing voices - voices that Command, comment or maintain dialogue.
Neither optical hallucinations are not unusual.
The person is not able to distinguish between the important from the unimportant, the brain can filter out spurious signals, consciousness is flooded with emotions.
Like a dream opens the floodgates flooding psychosis, of ideas and fantasy, which come from the deepest layers of consciousness.
The perception of reality in psychosis is concentrated on the body, says Professor Thomas Fuchs, chief physician of the clinic general psychiatry, university clinic in Heidelberg.
A schizophrenic is located in the centre of the stage, everything has meaning directed at him.
At the same time, getting into a passive role, it becomes, like in a dream, overwhelmed by events and can actively shape.
It is therefore often feel threatened, manipulated and controlled.
Comparison with reality is not usually possible for them, they are a terrible reality, waking up is out of the question.
Once in a lifetime experience hallucinations
Otherwise than in a dream, she says, " but still the sensual and spatial structure of the fact that one sees in psychosis, substantially preserved. "
Wandering thoughts and hallucinations are based on reality and experience of alienation is a real framework.
Scientists are still puzzled as to why our brain is doing exactly the sort of twists.
Special conditions may result from one person to lose the fact that in the short - term relationship to reality, says Fuchs.
Not everyone, however, develop into psychosis.
It seems that there is a genetic disposition to schizophrenia, but studies on twins have shown that genes are not the only determining factor.
Scientists are based on the fact that disabled people have a minimum of brain damage.
We believe that in the early stage of development of the damage to the brain, for example, such as viral diseases of the mother during pregnancy, says Fuchs.
But it remains a mystery, as there is a failure of the system, which for years did not materialise.
Factors also play a role of the effects of the neighborhood - stress or traumatic experiences may be, if it is to her disposition.
Also hallucinogenic drugs can trigger psychosis, because the transmission system.
When our brains
Crazy is that their psychotronici suffers from hallucinations, and to get rid of them, and swallowed an expensive medication, while others give money for drugs to be gained, he says, a professor of psychology.
If the images we perceive as pleasant or unpleasant, is often just a matter of attitude.
Kasten collects for ten years, reports of hallucinations and in the last year, results in a book, " Die Welt in unserem Kopf " (the world in our head) .
Although hallucinations are the typical phenomena accompanying psychoses, but also surprisingly many other diseases.
In addition to the psychiatric disorders such as borderline personality or depressive illness often as migraine, epilepsy, multiple sclerosis or Alzheimer's or brain trauma.
Surprisingly, under certain conditions, and by a healthy person's brain.
Hallucinations, according to Kasten, consist of the contents of the ideas, which are normally suppressed.
Arise, when the part of the brain, which processes sensory perception, too little repressed or active, if our brains, or when there is a lack of stimulation.
Drugs can run this state as well as the brain damage or psychosis.
But also the withdrawal of stimulus, stress, worry about love or other more exceptional conditions.
In the most recent studies, and one third of respondents had reported that at least once in her life.
In the summer of 2005, Sarah K. 16 years old, lives in a small town in Mecklenburg - Vorpommern and walk to a nearby school.
In fact, a normal girl.
If there were not the patterns and voices.
The breaks may be that it will appeal to kolohnát with long, dark hair.
When he replies, looking at her classmates with a surprise - no one except her see and hear the boy.
This shy girl as a dreamer, but Sarah K., knows it.
He is awake, hears and sees the boy, just as they hear and see the girl sitting next to him in the bench.
He may even feel his presence, at least for a few moments.
It's a nice feeling, is like the boy.
I'm crazy? , he asks.
But he knows that this boy and other delusions are not real and disappears.
In the night are rather disappointing appearances
Delusions are often a burden.
When sitting in class, not how many times following the instruction as a teacher in her eyes and ears was a new classmate, but he said while all other audible and visible on the board of the mathematical equation.
At night the phenomena rather depressing.
While waiting in a dark room to sleep, which is rarely and too late, often can not distinguish, if it's awake or if, if the images he sees, grimacing, or cutting a girl with bleeding wounds on the hands and feet are open or closed.
Leave me alone, shouting at the figures.
Parents and friends say anything about it, thought it about her that was crazy.
The autumn 2009. Sarah K. is now 20 years old.
Last year she graduated high school and live with her boyfriend.
A year ago, hallucinations stopped.
Since that time she contacted on the Internet psychologist Kasten knows exactly that mad.
The images are also art of despair
If someone is socially isolated or had removed incentives will likely hallucinations, says Kasten.
I believe that the brain does not have enough work and cares for his own amusement.
Sarah, an only child, she was like a little girl, fear of the other children, often playing herself.
The hallucinations began in 13 when he learned that the man who called my dad from the days when she thinks is her own father.
Because the visual and acoustic hallucinations are active in the same brain regions that process the real sensations and sounds, for people like Sarah K. difficult to distinguish from each other and reality. " every experience, " says, " takes place in the brain, the reality shows there.
Hallucinations are also images that allow the brain occur, so the real work. "
Also the night dreams as a form of delusion.
Healthy people does not differ substantially from hallucinations in acute psychosis.
Unlike schizophrenics are psychologically healthy people will be able to identify their errors as unrealistic.
Kasten therefore advise their patients to evaluate the hallucinations as an extraordinary ability.
Border state between dreams and hallucinations
In our world concentrated too much on the consciousness is an imaginary experience, unfortunately, the majority patologizován, says Michael Schmidt - Degenhard, professor in Heidelberg and chief psychiatric and psychotherapy clinic - Florence Nightingale hospital in Düsseldorf.
Psychosis is heavy, útrpná disease, but it also provides positive, creativity - a mirage is also the art of despair.
Schmidt - Degenhard the so - called oneiroidní form of experiences, a special form of altered consciousness to dream.
Oneiroidní states are highly complex, detailed fictional dreams, which is considered to be the real issue and can not be distinguished from or re - waking state.
Oneiroidní consciousness arises in the extreme situations caused by trauma or disease, such as inflammation polyradikulárním patients who experience the full knowledge of motor paralysis.
When a person is threatened by the loss of the world and herself, to be continued, the inability to move, replaced by the real life - threatening own, an imaginary world that is disconnected from reality, says Schmidt - Degenhard.
The type Species status of the borders between dreams and hallucinations.
Because in reality it is not possible to deal with any situation, there is a change in the world, the real situation but zpřítomní the idea.
The Intensive form of aid and the transfer of the senses in an intolerable situation, which allows people to our own ability to shape, move in an instant loss of consciousness.
Everything is real, and later in the memory
Also, the art historian Peter Cornelius Claussen oneiroidní describes his experiences in his book " the exchange " (heart) as a rescue mission of the soul.
He was 49 years old, when, after the heart valve surgery with subsequent heart transplantation published his consciousness on several track, with his body lay motionless on the intensive care unit.
Claussen plunged into a world he created, visited a foreign time and place: it is becoming an old man on the bed in a nursing home, the robot guarding his health.
He lives in the early Middle Ages, the nobility, which produces narcotic substances from the blood.
The bike he kidnaps Řek to their homeland, in a hospital bed in the Alps, and meets the Korean.
Completely immersed in the imaginary wrong, everything is real, and later in memory.
These internal travel for Claussena fundamentally different from any dream.
The dream is a different status, describes his experience.
In contrast to the dreams are memories of those mental disorders even after many years and non - essential details clearly obvious.
Even clearer and more intense than the actual experience.
The intensity of this experience shatters the horizon of our other opravdivých experience, says psychiatrist Schmidt - Degenhard.
After all, show oneiroidní states, psychosis, hallucinations and drug intoxication, how fragile are also waking up our internal images of external reality.
Any change in the state of consciousness, summarises the psychologist Kasten, " may lead to distortion of what we call reality. "
The fact that can also be rewarding.
