Promise FonPeek
Peek is extremely limited, only serves to explore the mail, without the ability to view a particular type of attachments or surfing the web.
Enjoyed his five minutes of fame in the U. S., when Time magazine praised it as one of the products of the year.
It is difficult to see him out there, but the idea may be interesting, especially for young people.
Unlike the Peek is characterised by a very low price and the monthly payments, less than half the amount, for example, for the data plan for the iPhone.
After his success, the company has started offering two new devices: one is designed exclusively for Twitter and the other on the basis of the data services provided free of charge, for which it is necessary to pay for the Peak amount.
FonPeek, which was presented yesterday to the Web site, is the European version of the invention, and at the same time, his third transformation.
It is limited, as well as his American counterpart, but it brings a surprise.
Monthly price for maintenance is around 12 euros a month and includes roaming across Europe.
The people of the passengers already know what it means to lose data services after crossing the border or impatiently search café with WiFi connection (or Fon) , so they can see the mail.
The idea of rooming with a fixed price is incredibly attractive and should be put in place for a long time ago.
Yes, some operators have special contracts and travel plans, but in my experience, one would need a doctorate in physics, in order to understand them, and very good glasses so he could read the tiny letters.
The European Commission has requested to reduce roaming tariffs so that they are accessible to the whole of Europe, which still does not have the desired effect.
There is justified concern about the use of data services outside the home state.
The fact that such a device as FonPeek (it is interesting that remains is the name Fon, he does not have this type of fare, means that operators are beginning to think otherwise and considering the various offers, kterýmiby compensate for its data network.
Kindle is another nice example, offers downloads of books and other search on the Internet.
No contract, no complications.
This device is connected and pay for the purchase, rather than months.
And that's exactly what I expect that one comes in, it is a possibility to purchase permanent access to the peek has already been introduced in the U. S..
Not because I wanted to buy it.
I am looking through the mail, on the phone, thank you.
I expect it, because I think that it's from the point of view of the consumer, the best type.
It would be interesting if the same system used in the computer.
