75% of working mothers have to work problems associated with maternity.
Discrimination in employment has increased in recent years, especially in younger women who intend to buy a child.
This is the result of the study's fertility and the working lives of Spanish women ', which, in cooperation with the Institute for women.
The study included 9737 women aged 15 to 75 years and the results are clear: 75% of working mothers have limited options in the labour market because of motherhood.
The study stresses that at the beginning of the partnership co - existence are many differences of opinion on the number of children, depending on whether they work or not, and also according to the type of employment.
Women who do not work outside the home, working part - time or do not have a stable job, starting with a partner to live before their first child before giving birth and generally have more children.
From the other side, women with stable employment, especially in the public sector, the partner coexistence and maternity postpone, and have fewer offspring.
" Women from 35 to 49 years with a stable job with their first child at an average of 3.7 years from the beginning of living with a partner. the figure of 4.1 for women, kterédosažení his stable job to pay the greater part of my life and, therefore, had to postpone and the arrival of children.
The type of employment is also a strong influence on maternity, although a smaller influence on the opening of living with a partner, " said Delgado, who is devoted to research in the CSIC.
Another factor affecting the age of women at the time of the marriage of a child is the level of education.
Research indicates that the higher the level of education, the higher is the age when women marry and have their first child.
The differences are also among the women of the same generation.
For example, in the age group of 35 to 49 years, women with the basic and higher education given birth to their first child at the age of 25.1 32.1.
" There is another difference between women depending on their level of education.
Women with primary education to marry and bear their first child before they find a stable job, while women with secondary or higher education act opposite prefer to obtain stable employment before marriage and birth of first child ", says Delgado.
