We do not understand where you happened to good manners, respect for animals and people.
Michelin and Fesvial together for the use of helm
Tyre manufacturer Michelin, in cooperation with the Spanish Foundation for Traffic safety (Fesvial) launched a campaign to promote the of Helm, especially for the younger motorists, now both of these bodies have informed.
The purpose of this initiative is to highlight the importance of the use of helmets, since it is the only means by which to prevent head injuries or death in the event of an accident while riding a motorcycle.
The company notes that this campaign is part of their obligations regarding the transport safety, which " means more than designing and producing a safer products ", and confirmed that it seeks to fulfil this purpose and otherwise, i. e. in the form of training and information campaigns.
This new campaign to promote the use of helmets when riding a motorcycle, under the slogan ' to be or not to be ' is the first phase, in which more than 500 motorcycles will be deployed fixed boards to get to the attention of the general public.
And at the end of the company warned that transport safety is a constant problem " of the company, which is a producer of tyres for cars and the main aim of which is the continuous improvement of the safety of products.
The sales of light commercial vehicles
After nearly two years, the market is beginning to recover light - duty vehicles.
All vehicles registered in November in Spain resulted in an increase of 12.6% compared to 2008, and what's more this is the first increase after 22 months of continuous decline, according to the figures of the organisation of the producers and retailers Ganvam.
The positive data, however, it is better to put in quarantine since November 2008 is very bad period for comparison and a 60% reduction compared with the previous year.
The result is that, despite the rise in the last month, the total number of registered vehicles in the last 11 months is about 40% less than in the previous financial year.
Since January, prodáno95. 853 vehicles, which includes all kinds of vehicles falling within the category of light commercial vehicles: derivatives of passenger cars, pick ups, vans, small trucks and light trucks/bogies.
And not even the gloom, or the most damaging inquiry, even if bought by private individuals, the majority of purchases made small and medium - sized enterprises and almost 100% of the cases, the financing through third parties.
The constraints resulting from the closure of bank loans, the source must be added other factors such as the cessation or continuation of bad economic situation.
In this situation, unlike cars, support for the purchase of 2000E helped too.
In addition to private individuals, it is to be noted iosoby business to business license small and medium - sized businesses, which they intend to buy a car of 3.5 tonnes of CO2 emissions levels exceeding 160 grams per kilometer, but the number of operations has been confirmed.
Just yesterday from Ganvamu again reminded of the need to pay special attention to the management of these vehicles, as well as industrial vehicles (trucks and buses) .
Sellers Association expects that 2010 will be to develop similar to the same as last year, according to the calculations, the sale of passenger cars and 4x4 drops by 19%.
Support system for the hand - brake is already mandatory equipment.
As in the case of antiblokovacího ABS system, it will be with the ESP stability control, auxiliary systems of the hand brake, it all becomes mandatory equipment of European cars.
In fact, form part of the compulsory installation of all newly registered passenger cars and light commercial vehicles, while the other is determined by the deadline for the removal of the shortage, which is February 2011.
The measures introduced in the EU aims to enhance the protection of pedestrians, the works so that it can help to avoid the many collisions.
The hand brake system increases the pressure on the brakes in an emergency, this system detects when the driver presses.
But not always able to keep this pressure until the end.
According to a study carried out by the manufacturer of automotive parts Bosch, a third of the drivers who have an accident, nesešlápli brake before the collision, and half of them did not use the full power of the brakes.
Up to 1100 accident
On the contrary, this assistance requires maximum braking systems, reducing the stopping distance of the vehicle.
According to a study conducted in the EU itself, if all vehicles were equipped with this type of equipment, it could be avoided and 1 100 fatalities per year related to pedestrians.
Reducing this number will be even more marked - from calculations in order to prevent one of the four incidents affecting the person - after the introduction of the so - called intelligent systems handbrake.
In this case, the vehicle is fitted with a system that (using radar or cameras) captures the obstacles and reports that the driver, except for a light braking.
If the driver responds, it will help to increase the pressure on the pedal, if it is needed.
If the driver does not react, even in the case where a collision can not be avoided, the device will be what impressed on the brakes and reduce the risk of damage to a minimum.
