Brazil has set a date for departure Zelayova
Brazil's government has set a deadline of remaining Manuel Zelaya on its embassy in Tegucigalpa.
Deposed president must leave the diplomatic mission not later than 27 January 2010, when its mandate officially ends.
Francisco Catunda, chargé d'affaires of the Brazilian embassy in the Honduran capital, confirmed for TV Globo, that " Mel " knows that he must leave by that date from the embassy, where he's hiding from 21 September.
" He is aware that the January 27 following the end of his mandate to leave and find other shelter.
The station also quoted a former statesman, who confirmed his intention to leave the embassy before the deadline: " I intend to leave as soon as possible, under the auspices of the Brazilian government, " he said by telephone.
After the election, 29 November (when he was elected Porfirio Lobo) Zelaya assured that remain in the Brazilian embassy until January.
However, the same week tried to obtain refuge in Brazil.
The operation has failed, because the condition Zelaya refused political asylum, which he tried to save the government " de facto ", chaired by Roberto Micheletti.
